{{Use British English|date=January 2017}} {{Infobox musical artist | name = Anne Lise Frøkedal | image = | image_size = | landscape = | alt = | caption = | background = solo_singer | birth_date = 19 July 1981 | alias = Frøkedal | origin = [[Etne]], [[Norway]] | genre = [[Folk music|Folk]], [[Folk music|Folk-pop]], [[Singer-Songwriter]] | instruments = Vocals, Guitar | years_active = {{start date|2015}}–present | label = [[Propeller Recordings]] | associated_acts = [[Harrys Gym|Harry's Gym]], I Was A King | website = {{URL|frokedal.com/}} | past_members = }}
'''Anne Lise Frøkedal''' known by her stage name '''Frøkedal''' is a folk-pop, singer-songwriter from [[Norway]].
Previously known as a member of acclaimed Norwegian bands [[Harrys Gym|Harry's Gym]] and "I Was A King", in 2015 she debuted as a solo artist. Releasing a series of singles and an EP in 2015, she released her debut album ''Hold On Dreamer'' in 2016. The album was later nominated for a [[Spellemannprisen]] - also known as the Norwegian [[Grammy Award|Grammys]] - for best Indie Album Of The Year 2017.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://musicnorway.no/2017/01/06/spellemann-nominations-announced/|title=Spellemann nominations announced|last=Buflaten|first=Erlend|date=6 January 2017|work=Music Norway|accessdate=11 January 2018}}</ref>
In 2017, Frøkedal announced her return with the release of singles ''Stranger'', and double single ''LTF/Cracks''.
Frøkedal released her second album, 'How We Made It' on August 31 2018. It received support from The 405, CLASH Magazine and The Line of Best Fit.
